from typing import List

class Solution:
    def destCity(self, paths: List[List[str]]) -> str:
        # Create a set of all starting cities
        starting_cities = set(path[0] for path in paths)

        # The destination city will be the one that is not in the starting cities
        for path in paths:
            if path[1] not in starting_cities:
                return path[1]
```

This solution works by first creating a set of all cities that are starting points of a path. Since the destination city is the only city that is not a starting point, we can find it by checking which city in the list of destinations is not in the set of starting cities.
